[[!meta title="The way to dusty death"]]
[[!tag books books/action]]

This is one of the books that Alistair Maclean wrote when he thought
he was writing screenplays, not books -- very visual action,
inscrutable and inhuman protagonists, improbable or missing plots, and
quite entertaining in a brainless kind of way. Yup, guilty pleasures.
